OL,3,CNHS trust 'fully accepts' watchdog
OL,4,Crecommendations after killer care
OL,6,FThe CQC highlighted that concerns
OL,7,Fraised by Calocane's family were "not
OL,8,Fconsistently acted on" by the trust
OL,9,Fand risk assessments did not "not make
OL,10,Fexplicit the serious nature" of the
OL,11,Frisk Calocane posed.
OL,13,FIt also found that the decision to
OL,14,Fdischarge Calocane to his GP "did not
OL,15,Fadequately consider" his risk of
OL,16,Frelapse.
OL,18,FMr Majid said: "As an organisation we
OL,19,Ffully accept those areas where we
OL,20,Fmissed opportunities.
