OL,4,Crecommendations after killer care
OL,6,F"What happened to them should not be
OL,7,Fexperienced by any family. I am
OL,8,Fcommitted to do everything in my power
OL,9,Fto prevent such a tragic event
OL,10,Freocurring, and I absolutely recognise
OL,11,Fthe obvious pain and suffering they
OL,12,Fcontinue to endure.
OL,14,F"I acknowledge that we have not got
OL,15,Fevery decision right, but we aim to be
OL,16,Fa learning organisation that benefits
OL,17,Ffrom feedback and challenges.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
